On Tue, 15 Jan 2013, Matthew Seaman wrote:
> I've just pushed fixes to pkgng HEAD on GitHub for checking security and
> access levels to the package DB, both for the INSTALL_AS_USER and
> various other use cases:

Thanks!

> Please test.

I extracted the patch from upstream via
  git show 6c1fc731a8013f046c2b061d7790cce869f4a6d0
and saved it into ports-mgmt/pkg/files, alas that gives
  ===>  Patching for pkg-1.0.4_1
  ===>  Applying FreeBSD patches for pkg-1.0.4_1
  2 out of 2 hunks failed--saving rejects to libpkg/pkgdb.c.rej
  => Patch patch-175249 failed to apply cleanly.
  *** [do-patch] Error code 1

So I figured I'd see how to directly build upstream, checked it
out and ran make (on ref10-i386.freebsd.org):

  pkg_config.c:299:3: error: comparison of integers of different signs:
      'unsigned int' and 'ssize_t' (aka 'int') [-Werror,-Wsign-compare]
                HASH_FIND(hhkey, conf_by_key, sbuf_data(b), sbuf_len(b), conf);
                ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
  /home/gerald/pkgng/libpkg/../external/uthash/uthash.h:101:8: note: expanded from
      macro 'HASH_FIND'
  ...HASH_FIND_IN_BKT((head)->hh.tbl, hh, (head)->hh.tbl->buckets[ _hf_bkt ],  \
     ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
  /home/gerald/pkgng/libpkg/../external/uthash/uthash.h:583:26: note: expanded
      from macro 'HASH_FIND_IN_BKT'
    if ((out)->hh.keylen == keylen_in) {...
        ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~ ^
  1 error generated.
  *** [pkg_config.o] Error code 1

Okay, so let's try GCC: env CC=gcc make
  cc1: warnings being treated as errors
  pkg_config.c: In function 'pkg_config_parse':
  pkg_config.c:299: warning: comparison between signed and unsigned
  *** [pkg_config.o] Error code 1

So I added some casts at external/uthash/uthash.h, line 583, and managed
to build with clang and pkg-static/pkg-static finally allowed me to test.


Good news: make INSTALL_AS_USER=1 install now works and with an empty
$PKG_DBDIR a new local.sqlite is created.


Bad news: pkg add some.txz fails with
  pkg: /home/gerald/porttest.PKG_DBDIR wrong user or group ownership
  Failure!

User and group for the directory look okay, though.

  ref10-i386:~> ls -lad /home/gerald/porttest.PKG_DBDIR
  drwxr-xr-x  2 gerald  devel  4096 Jan 19 17:03 /home/gerald/porttest.PKG_DBDIR
  ref10-i386:~> id -a
  uid=937(gerald) gid=493(devel) groups=493(devel),937(gerald)

Interestingly, this even happens with pkg info:

  ref10-i386:~> env PKG_DBDIR=/home/gerald/porttest.PKG_DBDIR ~/bin/pkg info
  pkg: /home/gerald/porttest.PKG_DBDIR wrong user or group ownership

So, I added some instrumentation to libpkg/pkgdb.c directly after this
error message, and oops!

  pkg: You are 0/0, the object is 937/493

Looking at the code above, I then found:

        if (install_as_user) {  
                euid = geteuid();
                egid = getegid();
        } else {
                euid = 0;
                egid = 0;
        }


This does not look right, and it's a regression when in the past neither 
pkg_add and definitely not pkg_info did these checks.  In fact, it is
also a regression within pkg itself, where pkg info also used to work
as a regular user (verified on the ref*.FreeBSD.org cluster).


Patch below.

If there is a different way for me to submit this, let me know.

Gerald


ChangeLog:
Always use the actual effective group and user ids when checking
access rights, instead of assuming 0/0 when INSTALL_AS_USER is not
set in the environment.  Remove the check for INSTALL_AS_USER.
Extend access right error message to show user and group ids.

diff --git a/libpkg/pkgdb.c b/libpkg/pkgdb.c
index 1457356..7ab69e6 100644
--- a/libpkg/pkgdb.c
+++ b/libpkg/pkgdb.c
@@ -6,6 +6,7 @@
  * Copyright (c) 2011-2012 Marin Atanasov Nikolov <dnaeon@gmail.com>
  * Copyright (c) 2012-2013 Matthew Seaman <matthew@FreeBSD.org>
  * Copyright (c) 2012 Bryan Drewery <bryan@shatow.net>
+ * Copyright (c) 2013 Gerald Pfeifer <gerald@pfeifer.com>
  * All rights reserved.
  *
  * Redistribution and use in source and binary forms, with or without
@@ -698,7 +699,7 @@ pkgdb_open_multirepos(const char *dbdir, struct pkgdb *db)
 }

 static int
-file_mode_insecure(const char *path, bool install_as_user)
+file_mode_insecure(const char *path)
 {
 	uid_t		euid;
 	gid_t		egid;
@@ -706,13 +707,8 @@ file_mode_insecure(const char *path, bool install_as_user)
 	bool		wrong_owner = false;
 	struct stat	sb;

-	if (install_as_user) {
-		euid = geteuid();
-		egid = getegid();
-	} else {
-		euid = 0;
-		egid = 0;
-	}
+	euid = geteuid();
+	egid = getegid();

 	if (stat(path, &sb) != 0) {
 		if (errno == EACCES)
@@ -747,7 +743,9 @@ file_mode_insecure(const char *path, bool install_as_user)
 		return (EPKG_INSECURE);
 	}
 	if (wrong_owner) {
-		pkg_emit_error("%s wrong user or group ownership", path);
+		pkg_emit_error("%s wrong user or group ownership "
+		               " (%d/%d versus %d/%d)",
+		               path, euid, egid, sb.st_uid, sb.st_gid);
 		return (EPKG_INSECURE);
 	}

@@ -770,7 +768,7 @@ database_access(unsigned mode, const char* dbdir, const char *dbname)

 	install_as_user = (getenv("INSTALL_AS_USER") != NULL);

-	retval = file_mode_insecure(dbpath, install_as_user);
+	retval = file_mode_insecure(dbpath);

 	database_exists = (retval != EPKG_ENODB);
